The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for superimposition of eye fundus images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of linear estimators and non-linear optimization, which are common techniques in machine learning and statistical analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of public health databases, which suggests a possible connection to human-computer interaction and healthcare, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another possible category. The paper also involves the use of image retrieval and analysis, which suggests a possible connection to information retrieval and multimedia, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia) other possible categories.
